Anyway, I don't let it get to me because I'd be missing out on a whole lot of laughs if I did.

The Katt Pack give viewers 2+ hours of guaranteed laughs. There was a time I thought Katt Williams would be doing what Kevin Hart is doing now - "leaving people in his dust". I still hold out hope that Katt Williams will continue doing what he does on a larger scale. In the meantime, Grab The Katt Pack and get ready for laughs.

This is a collection of Williams' material over the years so if you're a fan of his, you'll definitely love it. The only exception is "Katt Phenomenon" which is basically talking about him and his journey to where he is now. But, honestly, it's nothing that even a casual consumer of comedy doesn't already no about him. With that said, you have to ask yourself whether or not the price is worth the 3 discs since the 4th is essentially nothing. I've watched it once (after all, I did spend money on it) and can say with 100% certainty that I will never watch it again. The comedy dvd's are what you expect though- funny material.

Bottom line:
If you're a collector and you like Katt even a little, I'm pretty sure you won't regret the purchase.

Casual consumers: Looking for something funny for a night at home, this will do.

Katt is hilarious....this multi disc "pack" has some of his best stand up.  You get a large variety of subjects all with Katt's very funny take on things.  From recreational drug use, current events, and poking fun at celebrities to politics and child raising ....he covers it all.  He is so spot on with his comments and he is quite animated which adds to the comedy.  Be warned he is very much rated R though.  So, if you don't mind some profanity, wait let me say that again....if you don't mind lots of profanity he will make you laugh.
